HEADWORD: Cerebric
<hw>Cer"e*bric</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Of, pertaining to,
or derived from, the brain.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Cerebric acid</b></col> <fld>(Physiol. Chem.)</fld>,
<cd>a name formerly sometimes given to cerebrin.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cerebricity</ent>⟦br⟧
